SCAN 1: NON-UNIFORM BOUNDARY TYPES
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  Model: line of sight crosses N_s spheres, N_t tori, N_i irregular.
  Each type has its own correction: r_s, r_t, r_i.
  Total: H0_obs = H0_local * r_s^N_s * r_t^N_t * r_i^N_i

  Constraint: product = H0_CMB/H0_local = 0.92223439

  Hypothesis: sphere correction involves R2, torus involves R4.
    r_s = 1 - eps_s * R2 = 1 - eps_s * pi/4
    r_t = 1 - eps_t * R4 = 1 - eps_t * pi^2/32

  Fixed total N=100. Vary sphere/torus split.
  Assume eps_s = eps_t = eps (same magnitude, different R_n).

     N_s    N_t    N_i            eps          1-r_s          1-r_t
  ------ ------ ------ -------------- -------------- --------------
      90     10      0   0.0010974078  0.00086190205  0.00033846815
      80     20      0   0.0011732674  0.00092148204  0.00036186515
      70     30      0   0.0012603936  0.00098991078  0.00038873705
      60     40      0   0.0013614976   0.0010693177  0.00041992009
      50     50      0   0.0014802366   0.0011625751  0.00045654219
      30     70      0   0.0017929748   0.0014081991  0.00055299849
      10     90      0   0.0022732593   0.0017854137  0.00070113032

  Verification (product vs target):
     N_s    N_t        product         target
  ------ ------ -------------- --------------
      90     10     0.92220302     0.92223439
      80     20     0.92220184     0.92223439
      70     30     0.92220065     0.92223439
      60     40     0.92219948     0.92223439
      50     50      0.9221984     0.92223439
      30     70     0.92219706     0.92223439
      10     90     0.92219927     0.92223439

  KEY: eps ~ 0.00109741 for N_s dominant (sphere-dominated universe)
       eps ~ 0.00227326 for N_t dominant (torus-dominated universe)
  The eps range is ~factor 2 across splits.
  eps in units of alpha/(3pi) = 0.000774273:
    N_s=90, N_t=10: eps/base = 1.41734
    N_s=80, N_t=20: eps/base = 1.51531
    N_s=70, N_t=30: eps/base = 1.62784
